      • equals

        public static boolean equals​(com.google.gson.JsonElement expected,
                             com.google.gson.JsonElement actual)
        Checks whether the actual json element equals the expected one.

        Equality between json elements is defined as follows. If both elements are null, they are equal. If both elements are json primitives, they are only equal if they have the same value. If both elements are json objects, they are only equal if all fields of the actual json object exist in the expected one and if they have the same value in both objects. If both elements are json arrays, they are only equal if both have the same size and their corresponding elements are equal.

        Parameters:
        expected - an expected json element
        actual - an actual json element
        Returns:
        a boolean indicating whether the json elements are equal

      • equals

        private static boolean equals​(com.google.gson.JsonObject expected,
                              com.google.gson.JsonObject actual)
        Checks whether the actual json object equals the expected one.

        Json objects are only equal if all fields of the actual json object exist in the expected one and if they have the same value in both objects.

        Parameters:
        expected - an expected json object
        actual - an actual json object
        Returns:
        a boolean indicating whether the json objects are equal
